tool_description: Develop two way push messaging between IoT devices.
name: InstaMsg
title: InstaMsg

api_list.name: createClient

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The Client type. Takes any of the two values - `device` or `user`. `device` represents a IoT device client, and `user` represents a user client.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: Name of the tenant. For example, `Company 1`

required_parameters.name: provisioningId
required_parameters.description: Usually IMEI-Number for GPRS devices; MAC-ID for LAN and Wifi devices. But this can be any globally unique alpha-numeric string. For example, the device's UUID/Serial-Number.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: A short description of the Client.

optional_parameters.name: secureCertEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Will client-certificate-authentication take place when client connects to server. Can take values `true` or `false`.

optional_parameters.name: gsmApn
optional_parameters.description: This is the Access Point Name (APN) of the mobile network.

optional_parameters.name: provisioningKey
optional_parameters.description: An alphanumeric (0-9 and A-Z) key of length greater than 5 and less than 13. The key is case sensitive, therefore `KEY01` and `key01` are two different keys.

optional_parameters.name: gsmPassword
optional_parameters.description: The password for your APN.

optional_parameters.name: gsmSendSms
optional_parameters.description: If this field is `1`, the sms is sent to the GSM-device with the provisioning parameters.

optional_parameters.name: gsmSimPin
optional_parameters.description: The PIN for your SIM.

optional_parameters.name: gsmMsisdn
optional_parameters.description: The mobile phone number of the SIM that is used in the device, entered by the user in your app during provisioning process. Please note that here just the mobile-number should be entered, without any country-code or anything.

optional_parameters.name: gsmUsername
optional_parameters.description: The user name for your APN.

optional_parameters.name: gsmIsdCode
optional_parameters.description: Country-Code. For example, for India the code would be `+91`

optional_parameters.name: pubTopics
optional_parameters.description: List of pub topics to which the Client can publish messages to.

optional_parameters.name: subTopics
optional_parameters.description: List of sub topics to which the Client can subscribe.

api_list.name: createTenant

required_parameters.name: maxMessages
required_parameters.description: Max no of messages, which can be send by all clients of this tenant. This can be used to prevent abuse of messages by a tenant. Example from your purchase 1 million messages and you want to allot 10000 messages to this Tenant.

required_parameters.name: maxClients
required_parameters.description: Max no of clients, which can be created in this Tenant. This can be used effectively to ration clients for a tenant.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: A short description of your tenant.

api_list.name: deleteClient
deleteClientConfig
deleteFile
deleteTenant
downloadFile
getAccessToken
getClientAuthToken
api_list.description: Get Client Auth Token. You can get the auth token of Clients of type `user`.

api_list.name: getClientConfig
getClientInfo
getClientLogs
api_list.description: Client Logs are important to if you want to know what is happening at the client end (e.x. the client embedded in the IoT device) and the InstaMsg server end. You can use these logs to troubleshoot your clients.

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: The start date time (in unix-time in milliseconds)

optional_parameters.name: level
optional_parameters.description: Level of logs `DEBUG` , `INFO`, `WARN`, `ERROR`, `FATAL`.

optional_parameters.name: creator
optional_parameters.description: The creator of the logs. It can have two valid values `InstaMsg` and `client`.

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: The end date time (in unix-time in milliseconds)

api_list.name: getClientMetrics

optional_parameters.name: interval
optional_parameters.description: The interval over which the metrics should be aggregated. Valid value are `day` and `month`. `day` aggregates the metrics over last 24 hours while month over the last 30 days. The default is last 24 hours.

api_list.name: getClientNetworkLogs
api_list.description: InstaMsg Client libraries also push network information to the InstaMsg server. Network logs are very important to troubleshoot IoT device sites that have a poor network.

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: The end date time (in unix-time in milliseconds)

optional_parameters.name: iccid
optional_parameters.description: The sim number if the device has multiple sim cards.

optional_parameters.name: imei
optional_parameters.description: The imei of the network interface.

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: The start date time (in unix-time in milliseconds)

optional_parameters.name: macId
optional_parameters.description: Hexified-MAC-Id of the network interface.

optional_parameters.name: msisdn
optional_parameters.description: The mobile phone number if the device has multiple sim cards.

api_list.name: getClientSessions
api_list.description: You can get the client session details using the Client Sessions API.

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: The end date time, (in unix-time in milliseconds)

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: The start date time, (in unix-time in milliseconds)

api_list.name: getClients
getFiles
getMessages
api_list.description: You can list all messages exchanged by a client.

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: The start date time.

optional_parameters.name: type
optional_parameters.description: The message type. Takes any of the two values `pub` or `p2p`.

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: The end date time.

api_list.name: getSingleClient
getSingleTenant
getTenants

optional_parameters.name: active
optional_parameters.description: Possible values: 0, 1. Will list active or inactive tenants. If the filter is omitted it will return both active and inactive tenants.

api_list.name: invalidateAccessToken
publishMessage

required_parameters.name: payload
required_parameters.description: This is a UTF-8 encoded string. If your message contains characters not represented in UTF-8 encode your message in base64 or hex.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The message type. Values can be `pub`, `p2p`. To publish a message set it to `pub`.

required_parameters.name: id
required_parameters.description: The Message ID is a 16-bit unsigned integer that must be unique among the set of `in flight` messages in a particular direction of communication with a client. On your server side code you should maintain an map of client id, message id and reply handler or callback. When you receive a reply for a message. Set it to `null` for QOS 0 messages.

required_parameters.name: topic
required_parameters.description: Topic string can be any valid UTF-8 string of length limited to 64k. Topic string are case sensitive. So `TOPIC` and `topic` are two different topic.

required_parameters.name: qos
required_parameters.description: This is the Quality of Service (QOS) level for message delivery. Valid values are: `1`: AT MOST ONCE; `2`: AT LEAST ONCE; `3`: EXACTLY ONCE

optional_parameters.name: duplicate
optional_parameters.description: If you are re-sending this message set this to False i.e. 0.

optional_parameters.name: save
optional_parameters.description: If you want the message to be stored on InstaMsg cloud.

api_list.name: releaseMessage
api_list.description: Request InstaMsg to release (publish to subscribers) the message.
